<ssrf_advanced_vulnerability_guide>
<title>ADVANCED SERVER-SIDE REQUEST FORGERY (SSRF)</title>

<critical>Advanced SSRF exploitation focuses on cloud metadata services, DNS rebinding, blind SSRF with out-of-band validation, protocol smuggling, and SSRF-to-RCE chains. Master cloud-native attack surfaces and modern bypass techniques.</critical>

<scope>
- Cloud metadata exploitation (AWS IMDSv1/v2, GCP, Azure, Oracle Cloud)
- DNS rebinding attacks for bypassing localhost restrictions
- Blind SSRF with out-of-band (OOB) techniques
- Protocol smuggling (gopher, file, dict, ftp, jar, netdoc)
- SSRF to RCE chains via Redis, FastCGI, Docker, Memcached
- HTTP request smuggling combined with SSRF
- SSRF via SVG, PDF rendering, and image processing
</scope>

<methodology>
1. Map all input vectors that trigger server-side requests (URLs, webhooks, imports, previews, document processors)
2. Establish OOB channels (DNS, HTTP callbacks) for blind SSRF validation
3. Enumerate cloud provider detection and metadata endpoints
4. Test protocol handlers and parser differentials
5. Chain SSRF to achieve maximum impact (credentials, RCE, lateral movement)
</methodology>

